1. Install Arduino into Breadboard

2. Plug Arduino USB into Raspberry Pi

3. Open Arduino IDE:
   3a. Click raspberry icon in top-left corner of screen
   3b. Navigate to Programming>Arduino IDE
  
4. Check three settings under Tools menu:
  4a. Set "Board" to "Arduino Nano"
  4b. Set "Processor" to either "ATmega328P" or "ATmega328P (old bootloader)"
  4c. Set "Port" to "/dev/ttyUSBX"
  
5. In the Arduino IDE, go to the File menu, and select File>Examples>01 Basics>Blink

6. Go to the Sketch Menu, and select "Upload"

7. Verify the LED on the top of the Arduino is blinking once per second.
